      <title>[Letter] 1800 Jul. 7, Knoxville, Tennessee [to] David Henl[e]y / John Sevier</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>This document is a brief letter dated July 7, 1800 from governor John Sevier of Tennessee to David Henley, agent for the department of war. The purpose of the letter is a death allegedly caused by Indians in march of 1799. The governor requests any information Henley may have on the matter.</abstract>
